Inputs: 
    menu choice
    seat location (row and seat, or seat number)
    passenger name
    passenger age
    payment amount

Information being processed:
    check seat availability
    calculate price (base price, 20% discount if passenger younger than 7 or older than 65, 
        total plus tax (constant))
    compare payment to total (book or reject)
    compute the change denominations ($100, $50, $20, $10, $5, $1, quarters, dimes, nickels, pennies)
    make seat available and book new when change requested

Information Outputs:
    seating chart (available and taken with truncated names (12 chars), empty seats are empty strings)
    confirmation or rejection messages
    total cost
    change with breakdown (how many 100s, ...)
    message when no seats are available

Data Structures:
    two 2D lists (one for first class, one for coach)